OL,6,FInstead, the plan is likely to suggest
OL,7,Fthe period is simply to give the
OL,8,Femployee the ability to see if they
OL,9,Flike the job, and the employer the
OL,10,Fability to assess if the worker is
OL,11,Fsufficiently capable and qualified,
OL,12,Fwith a fair dismissal if the worker
OL,13,Ffalls short. Employers have argued
OL,14,Fthat a fair dismissal based on
OL,15,Fcapability is allowed after probation
OL,16,Fas well.
