OL,3,CWhat do we know about Labour's
OL,4,Cworkers' rights legislation?
OL,6,FA source claimed that some bosses were
OL,7,Fbeing "craven and unreasonable" at the
OL,8,Fmeeting - arguing the government had
OL,9,Fbent over backwards to include a
OL,10,Fprobation period in the first place,
OL,11,Fdespite union opposition. They claimed
OL,12,Fthere were "bad faith" arguments being
OL,13,Fmade.
OL,15,FThe shift on Thursday will also see
OL,16,Fimmediate access to sick pay, parental
OL,17,Fleave and protection from
OL,18,Fdiscrimination - as well as a ban on
OL,19,Fmost fire and rehire practices and
OL,20,F"exploitative" zero-hour contracts.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/8
