OL,3,CWhat do we know about Labour's
OL,4,Cworkers' rights legislation?
OL,6,FHowever, there will be some concerns,
OL,7,Fparticularly over the definition of
OL,8,Fexploitative zero-hour contracts - and
OL,9,Fhow wide they spread. Sources have
OL,10,Fsuggested the government is planning a
OL,11,Fcomplicated definition of what counts
OL,12,Fas exploitative.
OL,14,FUnions will be delighted with plans to
OL,15,Froll back limits on their powers put
OL,16,Fin place by the Conservative
OL,17,Fgovernment. Sources suggested the
OL,18,Fgovernment will also pave the way for
OL,19,Fonline strike ballots - which would
OL,20,Fhugely reduce the cost of balloting
OL,21,Ffor unions.
